    <item>
      <title>About</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/about/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/about/</guid>
      <description>&lt;section class=&#34;bg-gradient-to-b from-purple-50 via-purple-50 to-white pt-20 pb-32&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;container mx-auto px-4&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &#xD;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;text-center&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;h1 class=&#34;text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-6&#34;&gt;Advancing Global Population Health&lt;/h1&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;p class=&#34;text-xl text-gray-600 mb-16&#34;&gt;Bridging research and policy to address the critical intersections of population dynamics and human health&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;max-w-4xl mx-auto bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg p-10 md:p-12&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;            &lt;h2 class=&#34;text-3xl font-bold mb-6&#34;&gt;Our Mission&lt;/h2&gt;&#xD;&#xA;            &lt;p class=&#34;text-lg md:text-xl text-gray-600 leading-relaxed&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;                The Global Population and Health Association (GPHA) promotes equitable, evidence-based solutions to global challenges at the nexus of population change and health. We unite researchers, policymakers, and practitioners to transform knowledge into action for healthier populations worldwide.&#xD;&#xA;            &lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Join Us</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/join-us/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/join-us/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The Global Population and Health Association (GPHA) is an international nonprofit dedicated to advancing research, dialogue, and policy innovation at the intersections of population dynamics and human health. We translate robust evidence into equitable, resilient, and sustainable health solutions—working with universities, governments, civil society, and private partners worldwide.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;We’re seeking colleagues who care deeply about rigor, equity, and real-world impact.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Contact&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Email: &lt;a href=&#34;mailto:info@globalpophealth.org&#34;&gt;info@globalpophealth.org&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Address: Manfield House, 1 Southampton Street, London, WC2R 0LR, United Kingdom&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>News &amp; Policy Impact</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/news/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/news/</guid>
      <description>&lt;section class=&#34;py-16 bg-gradient-to-b from-white to-gray-50&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;container mx-auto px-4&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &#xD;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;max-w-6xl mx-auto text-center&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;h1 class=&#34;text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-6 text-gray-900&#34;&gt;News &amp; Policy Impact&lt;/h1&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;p class=&#34;text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;            Translating cutting-edge research into actionable policy recommendations for governments, organizations, and communities worldwide&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/section&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;section class=&#34;py-12&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;container mx-auto px-4&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &#xD;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;max-w-6xl mx-auto&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;!-- Featured Story --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;mb-16&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-600 to-blue-600 rounded-2xl p-1&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;                &lt;div class=&#34;bg-white rounded-2xl p-8&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;                    &lt;div class=&#34;flex items-center mb-4&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;                        &lt;span class=&#34;px-3 py-1 bg-red-100 text-red-700 rounded-full text-sm font-medium&#34;&gt;FEATURED&lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;                        &lt;span class=&#34;ml-3 text-gray-500&#34;&gt;September 2025&lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;                    &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;                    &lt;h2 class=&#34;text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-gray-900&#34;&gt;One Day of Work Per Week Sufficient for Mental Health Benefits&lt;/h2&gt;&#xD;&#xA;                    &#xD;&#xA;                    &lt;div class=&#34;grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;                        &lt;div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;                            &lt;p class=&#34;text-gray-700 mb-4&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;                                Our groundbreaking research, conducted with the University of Cambridge, has redefined understanding of the relationship between work and wellbeing. The study of over 70,000 UK residents reveals that just 8 hours of work per week provides the full mental health benefits of employment.&#xD;&#xA;                            &lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
